            <title>[HIVE-2113] In shell mode, local mode continues if a local-mode task throws exception in pre-hooks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-2113</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In Driver.execute(), if exception is thrown in prehooks, the execution jumps to the exception handling logic and skips the step of ctx.restoreOriginalTracker(). As a result, the next query will be executed as local mode no matter input size since the job tracker setting is not reverted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
